# Documentation: AI clarity hack

When asking AI to draft or rewrite articles, documentation, or how-tos, use this prompt (or equivalent):

**"Write this for 80 IQ people."**

Variants that work well:
- "Write so someone with no background can follow."
- "Explain every term the first time. Short sentences, one idea per step."
- "Rewrite for maximum clarity; assume the reader is not an expert."

This produces the clearest, most scannable docs: short sentences, jargon explained once, ordered steps, tables for copy-paste, and a quick "What do I need?" at the top. Add this instruction whenever you request new or rewritten documentation.
